data.title: Abrahamson Genealogy Site
data.text:
Death23 January 2016Marvin A. Friede died on 23 January 2016 at Englewood, Sarasota, Florida, at age 88 Marvin A. Friede 88 of Englewood, Florida died January 23, 2016. He was born December 23, 1927 in Madison, Wisconsin to Arthur and Violet Friede. He moved to the Englewood area in 1955 from Wisconsin. He was a member of Englewood United Methodist Church, a Life Member of the Englewood Elks Lodge, the Fraternal Order of Eagles and the Moose Lodge and he was a volunteer Fireman in Englewood years ago. He was a School Bus driver for Charlotte County for 14 years and worked for Culligan Water for 28 years. He loved his cat Oliver and all animals. He was an avid blood donor for many years and he loved to walk and visit friends. He married his wife Betty on August 29, 1948, she predeceased him in 2014, and also by his parents and four sisters, Loretta, Darlene, Dorothy and Laverne. He is survived by his daughter, Susan Newberry of Englewood, his son Gerry (Luann) Friede of Middleburg, Florida; grandchildren, Teata Bonfiglio, Eben Barnes and Billy Newberry; great-grandchildren, Spencer, Zach, Dylan and Emma. Visitation will be held on Wednesday from 11:00 a.m. until noon with funeral services to follow at Lemon Bay Funeral Home. Burial will be in Lemon Bay Cemetery.

Memorial donations may be made to TideWell Hospice. You may express your condolences to the family at lemonbayfh.com. Lemon Bay Funeral Home and Cremation Services is in charge of arrangements.Death23 October 1973Esther Perau died on 23 October 1973 at age 78 Esther McLerran, 167 Third St., Reedsburg died Tuesday, October 23, 1973 after a long illness. She was born in Reedsburg to Henry Perau and Bertha Krohn. She married Hubert S. McLerran who died on December 4, 1960. She was a clerk at Allis Chalmers in Milwaukee and a member of St. Peter's Lutheran church. Services by the Gant Funeral Home, were held on Friday, October 26, with Rev. Dennis Hipenbecker officiating. Burial followed at St. Peter's Cemetery. Survivors include 1 sister, (Alta) Mrs. Ewald Rosenthal, Reedsburg. Taken from the Reedsburg paper of November 8, 1973.
